{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":"Consider the function $C$ : $\\mathbb{N} â†’ \\mathbb{N}$\nThe Collatz Map $C(n)$ is defined to be:\n\n$$ C(n) = \\begin{cases} n / 2, & \\text{if } n \\equiv 0 (mod 2), \\\\ \n3n + 1  & \\text{if } n \\equiv 1 (mod 2), \\\\\n1 & \\text{if } n = 1 \\end{cases} \n$$\n \n\nWhere a Collatz sequence is:"}
{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":1,"metadata":{"collapsed":false,"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"source":"#Import relevant modules to be used within the code\nimport numpy as np\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nfrom exercise1 import collatz\n #Allows plots to be displayed within notebook\n%matplotlib inline"}
{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":2,"metadata":{"collapsed":false,"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"source":"#Create an array for the stopping times for each Collatz sequence\nstoppingTime = []\nfor i in range(1, 5001, 1):\n    seq = collatz(i)\n    stoppingTime.append(len(seq) - 1)"}
{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":3,"metadata":{"collapsed":false,"trusted":true},"outputs":[{"data":{"text/plain":"<matplotlib.text.Text at 0x7fcc0cd42d90>"},"execution_count":3,"metadata":{},"output_type":"execute_result"},{"data":{"image/png":"smc-blob::3c061ab0-c8fa-4a1c-8c39-af1a5dd2c492","text/plain":"<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x7fcc0c4efbd0>"},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"}],"source":"#Make an array of integer values \n#Plot against the corresponding stopping times\ninteger_n = np.arange(1, 5001, 1)\nplt.scatter(integer_n, stoppingTime, c='blue')\nplt.grid(b=True, which='both', color='0.65', linestyle='--')\nplt.xlabel('$n$')\nplt.ylabel('Stopping Time')\nplt.title('Scatter Plot of the Stopping Times of the Collatz Map\\n plotted for the first 5000 natural numbers\\n')"}
